    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <head>2. Telegram 312 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d2fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/7–2955. Limited Official Use.
                        Drafted by Kreer (SS).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-07-29">July 29, 1955, 7:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d2-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d2-1"/>
                <p>312. Essential Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName> have
                    full freedom telegraphic communications with Department and interested posts
                    during forthcoming Chinese discussions. Following procedures will apply:</p>
                <p>Telegrams will be numbered in regular consulate series without external
                    designator but carrying internal caption for or from <persName
                        corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Outgoing telegrams will be signed <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">Gowen</persName>.
                    This will not imply or require consulate concurrence nor should any such
                    telegrams receive any distribution within consulate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
